Upstream kernel files are kept verbatim
---------------------------------------

The core sources (ga.py, agent_loop.py, agentmain.py, llmcore.py, simphtml.py,
TMWebDriver.py, frontends/*, the memory/* tools, and the assets/* the kernel
actually loads at runtime), together with the root pyproject.toml and LICENSE,
are upstream GenericAgent files kept at deliberate zero diff so that upstream
kernel updates merge cleanly.

As a distribution, Penglai curates the tree: upstream files that only describe
or promote the GenericAgent project itself (its own README, docs/, demo media,
community QR codes, technical report) are not part of running the distro and are
not carried here. The repository's front page is this repo's root README.md
(Penglai-branded). Penglai's only install entry points are install.sh /
docker-install.sh / the PyPI bootstrap (installer/), all pointing at
kevinchennewbee/PenglaiAgent.


